text: Temiskaming Shores is a city in the Canadian province of Ontario. It was created in 2004 by the merger of the town of New Liskeard, the town of Haileybury, and the township of Dymond. In 2021, 9,634 people lived in Temiskaming Shores. Haileybury is the seat of Timiskaming District. About 66% of the people in Temiskaming Shore speak English as the mother language, while 28% of the people speak French as a mother language. == References == Category:Cities in Ontario
